00:11:28,574 --> 00:11:30,656
This is how Rost looked like for most of production.

221
00:11:31,517 --> 00:11:33,338
This guy, you know, he even snuck into one of the trailers.

222
00:11:33,999 --> 00:11:35,499
and we kept using generic Ross,

223
00:11:35,519 --> 00:11:36,939
you know, we kept keeping him generic

224
00:11:37,279 --> 00:11:39,440
because things were staying in flux for the longest time.

225
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:41,961
And we really waited until stuff

226
00:11:41,981 --> 00:11:43,101
was only really coming together,

227
00:11:43,141 --> 00:11:44,941
which was really only a couple of months before alpha,

228
00:11:45,741 --> 00:11:47,982
before we started selecting the characters like Ross,

229
00:11:48,302 --> 00:11:49,983
who needed that bespoke content the most.

230
00:11:51,743 --> 00:11:53,423
And then we would start doing, you know,

231
00:11:53,483 --> 00:11:55,524
very specific designs who really nailed

232
00:11:55,544 --> 00:11:57,404
who these characters, you know, really were.

233
00:11:57,424 --> 00:11:59,705
And in Ross' case, you know,

234
00:12:00,285 --> 00:12:02,246
this is about making him look a bit more paternal

235
00:12:02,286 --> 00:12:03,266
than we originally envisioned.

236
00:12:03,864 --> 00:12:07,026
But it was also about communicating his weird relationship with the rest of the tribe.

237
00:12:07,066 --> 00:12:10,630
You see, Rost, he's a very kind of conservative, very traditional Noor,

238
00:12:11,050 --> 00:12:12,572
but he's also an outcast from the tribe.

239
00:12:12,612 --> 00:12:15,514
So his design is to strike that difficult balance between, you know,

240
00:12:15,574 --> 00:12:17,156
keeping Noor traditions on one hand,

241
00:12:17,536 --> 00:12:19,398
but also separating him from the rest of the tribe.

242
00:12:20,239 --> 00:12:23,260
And if we didn't wait until we had all of that information,

243
00:12:23,901 --> 00:12:26,462
you know, his design would not have been as effective,

244
00:12:27,003 --> 00:12:28,724
his characterization wouldn't have been as strong,

245
00:12:29,584 --> 00:12:31,786
and, you know, the idea of who Ross was

246
00:12:31,826 --> 00:12:33,747
wouldn't have been as clearly communicated to the player.

